import sys

    num = int(sys.stdin.readline())
    heappush(heap, num)

while len(heap) > 1:
    a = heappop(heap)
    b = heappop(heap)
    heappush(heap, (a + b) / 2)

print(heap[0])

def averageOfTopEmployees(rating):
    count = 0
    for i in rating:
        if i >= 90:
            count += 1
    return count/len(rating)

def median(nums):
    nums.sort()
    if len(nums) % 2 == 0:
        return (nums[int(len(nums) / 2)] + nums[int(len(nums) / 2 - 1)]) / 2
    else:
        return nums[int(len(nums) / 2)]
